'''Abdallah Ra'ed Mahmoud Al-Fakhouri''' ({{langx|ar|عَبْد الله رَائِد مَحْمُود الْفَاخُورِيّ}}; born January 22, 2000) is a [[Jordan]]ian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Jordanian Pro League]] side [[Al-Wehdat SC|Al-Wehdat]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

Since his teenage years, he has been considered one of his country's most promising talents at his position.<ref name="kha">{{cite news|url=https://www.khaberni.com/news/%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AF-%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B4%D8%A9-%D8%A5%D8%B3%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%A9-234191|title=حارس اردني يستعد لمعايشة إسبانية|publisher=[[Khaberni]]|date=10 May 2018|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar}}</ref><ref name="contract">{{cite news|url=https://royanews.tv/news/159555?title=1531937069|title=الوحدات الأردني يعزز صفوفه بالحارس عبدالله الفاخوري|publisher=royanews.tv|date=18 July 2018|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://jo.gitsport.net/?p=26358|title=حارس الوحدات ومنتخب الشباب الفاخوري بديلا لياسن بالمنتخب|publisher=gitsport.net|date=22 December 2017|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar}}</ref>

==Club career==
Al-Fakhouri trialed with Belgian side [[Waasland-Beveren]] in June 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.palestinetoday.net/1189/194437-%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%AD%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%85%D8%B7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%A8-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%8A%D9%83%D9%8A|title=عبدالله الفاخوري حارس الوحدات الأردني مطلوب في الدوري البلجيكي|publisher=palestinetoday.net|date=28 June 2018|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar}}</ref> He had also received invitations from [[Real Valladolid]] in [[Spain]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://alrai.com/article/10431890/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%85%D9%86%D9%88%D8%B9%D8%A9|title=أخبار رياضية محلية منوعة - صحيفة الرأي|publisher=[[Al Ra'i (Jordanian newspaper)|Al Ra'i]]|date=8 April 2018|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar}}</ref> and [[Sporting CP|Sporting Lisbon]] in [[Portugal]].<ref name="rum">{{cite news|url=http://www.rumonline.net/print.php?id=383171|title=الفاخوري مطلوب لأندية أوروبية !!|publisher=rumonline.net|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar}}</ref> However, the following month, he signed his first professional contract, deciding to stay at [[Al-Wehdat SC|Al-Wehdat]] on a four-year deal.<ref name=contract/><ref name="saraya">{{cite news|url=https://www.sarayanews.com/article/497605|title=تعرف على خليفة "شفيع" الذي وقع معه الوحدات|publisher=[[Saraya (newspaper)|Saraya]]|date=19 July 2018|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar}}</ref> He is generally seen as the successor to [[Amer Shafi]].<ref name=saraya/><ref name="ammanjo">{{cite news|url=http://www.ammanjo.net/print.php?id=47033|title=الفاخوري يضع شرطا للاستمرار مع الوحدات|publisher=ammanjo.net|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar}}</ref>

On 16 January 2023, Al-Fakhouri joined Saudi Arabian club [[Al-Ain FC (Saudi Arabia)|Al-Ain]].<ref>{{cite web |title=نادي العين السعودي يعلن تعاقده رسميا مع الفاخوري |url=https://alghad.com/%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%87-%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D9%85/}}</ref>

He returned to Al-Wehdat on 5 July 2023.<ref>{{cite web |title=الوحدات يتفق مع الفاخوري | date=5 July 2023 |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1252310}}</ref>

==International career==

===Youth teams===
Al-Fakhouri led the [[Jordan national under-20 football team|national under-19 team]] to an appearance in the [[2018 AFC U-19 Championship]], finishing in first place in [[2018 AFC U-19 Championship qualification#Group E|their qualifying group]].<ref name=kha/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://assabeel.net/news/2017/11/13/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%82%D8%B9-%D8%B9%D9%82%D8%AF%D8%A7-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%AD%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%82%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A8%D8%A7|title=الفاخوري: سأوقع عقداً مع الوحدات قريباً|first=Thaer|last=Mustafa|publisher=[[Assabeel]]|date=13 November 2017|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar}}</ref>

Al-Fakhouri was named in Jordan's squad for the [[2022 AFC U-23 Asian Cup]].

===Senior team===
Before even playing with the [[Al-Wehdat SC|Al-Wehdat]] first team, Al-Fakhouri was called up to the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan senior national team]] in late 2017 for the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup qualification – third round|third round]] of [[2019 AFC Asian Cup qualification]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.jfa.com.jo/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B7%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%AE%D8%AA%D8%AA%D9%85-%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%B3%D9%83%D8%B1%D9%87-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%AF%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%BA/|title=المنتخب الوطني يختتم معسكره في دبي.. ويغادر الى طاجيكستان|publisher=[[Jordan Football Association]]|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181221134736/https://www.jfa.com.jo/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B7%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%AE%D8%AA%D8%AA%D9%85-%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%B3%D9%83%D8%B1%D9%87-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%AF%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%BA/|archive-date=21 December 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.al-sharq.com/news/details/510020|title=عبد الله الفاخوري في تصريح للشرق: حلمي تحقق بالانضمام إلى النشامى|first=Fadi|last=Al Amri|publisher=[[Al Sharq]]|date=30 August 2018|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar}}</ref>

He made his senior international debut on 11 January 2018, replacing [[Yazid Abu Layla]] during a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] 1–2 defeat to [[Finland national football team|Finland]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://alrai.com/article/10420749/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D9%81%D9%86%D9%84%D9%86%D8%AF%D8%A7-(2)-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%86-(1)-%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85--%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%A6%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D9%85%D9%86%D9%82%D9%88%D8%B5%D8%A9|title=فنلندا (2) الأردن (1) ودياً بكرة القدم .. فائدة منقوصة|first=Habis|last=Al Jarrah|publisher=[[Al Ra'i (Jordanian newspaper)|Al Ra'i]]|date=12 January 2018|accessdate=20 December 2018|language=ar}}</ref> At 17 years old, he became the youngest goalkeeper in Jordan's history.<ref name=rum/>

Al-Fakhouri was named in Jordan's squad for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]].

Al-Fakhouri was named in Jordan's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].

